            <handDesc hands="1">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" medium="unknown" scope="sole" script="syr">
                <desc>This manuscript is written in a good, regular hand of the <origDate notBefore="0800" notAfter="1000">ixth or xth cent.</origDate></desc>
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <p/>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <locus from="56a"/>
                  <p>On fol. 56 a is the following note in a good Arabic hand:</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="ar"><choice><sic>نضر</sic><corr resp="http://syriaca.org/documentation/editors.xml#wwright">(نظر)</corr></choice> في هذا الكتاب واحد خاطي وكتب منه شيءِ <foreign xml:lang="en">(sic)</foreign> قليل عن الاخبار الاوله</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="56b"/>
                  <p>On fol. 56 b is an older Syriac note, stating that the book
                                        once belonged to a priest named <persName>Yāyē</persName>: </p>
                  <p>
                                        <quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܕܝܐܝܐ ܩܫܝܫܐ ܕܝܪܝܐ
                                            ܐܟܣܢܝܐ ܟܠ ܕܩܪܐ ܨܠܐ.</quote>
                                    </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
